  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Meeting Transcript Speaker Visualization with Color-Coded Turn Segmentation\n\nEnhance the Transcript tab within the Meeting Details flyout/sidebar panel to visually differentiate speakers using color coding and restructure the raw transcript text into discrete, speaker-attributed turn segments.\n\nRequirements:\n\nSpeaker Color Assignment:\n- Dynamically assign a distinct color per unique speaker detected in the transcript data\n- Use a predefined palette of accessible, high-contrast colors that work in both light and dark mode (leverage existing color system tokens)\n- Ensure color assignments are stable within a session (same speaker always gets same color throughout the transcript)\n- Support gracefully degrading to a neutral color for unidentified or \"Unknown\" speakers\n\nSpeaker Turn Segmentation:\n- Parse the transcript and group consecutive lines/sentences by speaker into discrete turn blocks\n- Each turn block must display: speaker name (or label), timestamp or time range of the turn, and the spoken content\n- Merge consecutive segments from the same speaker into a single visual block (avoid fragmenting one speaker's turn into multiple cards)\n- Preserve chronological order of the full conversation\n\nVisual Design:\n- Display a colored left-border or avatar/badge beside each turn block to indicate the speaker\n- Show the speaker name as a label above or beside each turn block, styled in their assigned color\n- Render timestamps in a muted, secondary style to avoid visual noise\n- Ensure turn blocks are clearly separated with adequate whitespace\n- Do not alter the existing tab navigation structure (Transcript / Key Points / Action Items tabs remain unchanged)\n\nSpeaker Legend:\n- Add a compact speaker legend or key at the top of the transcript tab listing each speaker and their assigned color\n- Clicking a speaker name in the legend should filter/highlight only that speaker's turns (others dimmed), with a toggle to show all\n\nEdge Cases to Handle:\n- Transcripts with a single speaker (no segmentation needed; still apply color)\n- Very long speaker turns spanning many paragraphs\n- Speaker names that are long strings or contain special characters\n- Transcripts where speaker metadata is absent or malformed — fall back gracefully to unsegmented plain text rendering\n- Empty transcript state (no change to existing empty state UI)\n\nData Considerations:\n- Audit the existing transcript data shape returned from the Krisp webhook and stored in Neon PostgreSQL to confirm whether speaker attribution is already structured (e.g., array of `{ speaker, timestamp, text }` objects) or needs to be parsed from a raw string\n- If parsing is required, implement a robust regex or split strategy that handles common Krisp transcript formats (e.g., \"Speaker Name: text\" or timestamped blocks)\n- No new API endpoints required if transcript data is already fetched for the flyout; extend the existing data pipeline only if speaker fields are missing\n\nAccessibility:\n- Do not rely on color alone to distinguish speakers — pair color with speaker name labels and/or distinct avatar initials\n- Ensure color contrast ratios meet WCAG AA standards for text on background\n\n\n",
  "title": "Add color-coded speaker segmentation to meeting transcripts",
